cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR 

This paper discusses the comparison of deep learning models for semantic segmentation on remote sensing images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a viable on-orbit semantic segmentation strategy, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) in the aerospace industry. Additionally, the paper discusses the computing environment of satellites, which is related to the field of graphics (cs.GR).
